<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <prefix>§</prefix>
  <num>20-311</num>
  <heading proof="needed">Nature of proceeding.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Upon request for abbreviated probate contained in a petition for probate, the Register of Wills:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>May admit a will to probate; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Shall appoint one or more personal representatives based on the statements contained in the petition for probate.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>The Register of Wills may require additional verified proof, which shall be filed in the proceeding.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(c)</num>
    <text>The finality of abbreviated probate shall be governed by <cite path="§20-331">§ 20-331</cite>.</text>
  </para>
